summary: Planning, design and construction of ports and harbour infrastructure. Responsible for managing numerous multi-disciplinary port development projects around the world as maritime consultant. The majority of these projects being; oil and gas terminals, container terminals, dry bulk terminals, marina's, naval bases, land reclamation and coastal protection projects. Previously based permanently in the Middle East and Northern Africa region for over ten years.

Project value: AED 650,000,000

Project Description:
Realization of a new Marine Oil Terminal with four berths able to receive Aframax to VLCC size tankers. The work comprised of the construction of 1,500m of quay wall (Combi retaining Wall) with a retaining height of 23m, dredging of 5 million m3 to bring the new harbour basin to -18m depth and backfilling of the terminal area and the construction of a 1,000m long breakwater at a water depth of -21m.

MUC Engineering role:
- Masterplan development of Oil Terminal 2
- All structural, geotechnical and hydraulic designs
- Preparation of tender documents and guiding of tender phase
- Project supervision and management

Contractor:
Athena SA with NMDC as dredging subcontractor
